item.title: Weekly: What’s next for science in 2024? A year of moons; weight-loss drugs; and a massive new supercomputer for Europe
item.description:
#231

It’s a new year and that means new science. But what (that we know so far) does 2024 hold? 

On the space front, agencies around the world have as many as 13 missions to Earth’s moon, while Japan’s MMX mission will launch to take samples from the Martian moon Phobos.
